title: Smoking in pregnancy, United Kingdom, 2007/08
name: Smoking in pregnancy, United Kingdom, 2007/08
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on smoking in pregnancy. Smoking in pregnancy has well known detrimental effects for the growth and development of the baby. Encouraging pregnant women to stop smoking during pregnancy may also help them kick the habit for good, and thus provide health benefits for the mother. The percentage of women giving birth in 2007/08 who are current smokers at the time of delivery out of all maternities where smoking in pregnancy status is recorded.
